verses.text_plain: Be ye therefore followers of God, as dear children;
verses.verse_html: 1Be ye therefore followers of God, as dear children;

verses.text_plain: And walk in love, as Christ also hath loved us, and hath given himself for us an offering and a sacrifice to God for a sweetsmelling savour.
verses.verse_html: 2And walk in love, as Christ also hath loved us, and hath given himself for us an offering and a sacrifice to God for a sweetsmelling savour.

verses.text_plain: But fornication, and all uncleanness, or covetousness, let it not be once named among you, as becometh saints;
verses.verse_html: 3But fornication, and all uncleanness, or covetousness, let it not be once named among you, as becometh saints;

verses.text_plain: Neither filthiness, nor foolish talking, nor jesting, which are not convenient: but rather giving of thanks.
verses.verse_html: 4Neither filthiness, nor foolish talking, nor jesting, which are not convenient: but rather giving of thanks.

verses.text_plain: For this ye know, that no whoremonger, nor unclean person, nor covetous man, who is an idolater, hath any inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and of God.
verses.verse_html: 5For this ye know, that no whoremonger, nor unclean person, nor covetous man, who is an idolater, hath any inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and of God.

verses.text_plain: Let no man deceive you with vain words: for because of these things cometh the wrath of God upon the children of disobedience.
verses.verse_html: 6Let no man deceive you with vain words: for because of these things cometh the wrath of God upon the children of disobedience.

verses.text_plain: Be not ye therefore partakers with them.
verses.verse_html: 7Be not ye therefore partakers with them.

verses.text_plain: For ye were sometimes darkness, but now are ye light in the Lord: walk as children of light:
verses.verse_html: 8For ye were sometimes darkness, but now are ye light in the Lord: walk as children of light:

verses.text_plain: (For the fruit of the Spirit is in all goodness and righteousness and truth;)
verses.verse_html: 9(For the fruit of the Spirit is in all goodness and righteousness and truth;)

verses.text_plain: Proving what is acceptable unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 10Proving what is acceptable unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And have no fellowship with the unfruitful works of darkness, but rather reprove them.
verses.verse_html: 11And have no fellowship with the unfruitful works of darkness, but rather reprove them.

verses.text_plain: For it is a shame even to speak of those things which are done of them in secret.
verses.verse_html: 12For it is a shame even to speak of those things which are done of them in secret.

verses.text_plain: But all things that are reproved are made manifest by the light: for whatsoever doth make manifest is light.
verses.verse_html: 13But all things that are reproved are made manifest by the light: for whatsoever doth make manifest is light.

verses.text_plain: Wherefore he saith, Awake thou that sleepest, and arise from the dead, and Christ shall give thee light.
verses.verse_html: 14Wherefore he saith, Awake thou that sleepest, and arise from the dead, and Christ shall give thee light.

verses.text_plain: See then that ye walk circumspectly, not as fools, but as wise,
verses.verse_html: 15See then that ye walk circumspectly, not as fools, but as wise,

verses.text_plain: Redeeming the time, because the days are evil.
verses.verse_html: 16Redeeming the time, because the days are evil.

verses.text_plain: Wherefore be ye not unwise, but understanding what the will of the Lord is.
verses.verse_html: 17Wherefore be ye not unwise, but understanding what the will of the Lord is.

verses.text_plain: And be not drunk with wine, wherein is excess; but be filled with the Spirit;
verses.verse_html: 18And be not drunk with wine, wherein is excess; but be filled with the Spirit;

verses.text_plain: Speaking to yourselves in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing and making melody in your heart to the Lord;
verses.verse_html: 19Speaking to yourselves in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing and making melody in your heart to the Lord;

verses.text_plain: Giving thanks always for all things unto God and the Father in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ;
verses.verse_html: 20Giving thanks always for all things unto God and the Father in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ;

verses.text_plain: Submitting yourselves one to another in the fear of God.
verses.verse_html: 21Submitting yourselves one to another in the fear of God.

verses.text_plain: Wives, submit yourselves unto your own husbands, as unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 22Wives, submit yourselves unto your own husbands, as unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: For the husband is the head of the wife, even as Christ is the head of the church: and he is the saviour of the body.
verses.verse_html: 23For the husband is the head of the wife, even as Christ is the head of the church: and he is the saviour of the body.

verses.text_plain: Therefore as the church is subject unto Christ, so let the wives be to their own husbands in every thing.
verses.verse_html: 24Therefore as the church is subject unto Christ, so let the wives be to their own husbands in every thing.

verses.text_plain: Husbands, love your wives, even as Christ also loved the church, and gave himself for it;
verses.verse_html: 25Husbands, love your wives, even as Christ also loved the church, and gave himself for it;

verses.text_plain: That he might sanctify and cleanse it with the washing of water by the word,
verses.verse_html: 26That he might sanctify and cleanse it with the washing of water by the word,

verses.text_plain: That he might present it to himself a glorious church, not having spot, or wrinkle, or any such thing; but that it should be holy and without blemish.
verses.verse_html: 27That he might present it to himself a glorious church, not having spot, or wrinkle, or any such thing; but that it should be holy and without blemish.

verses.text_plain: So ought men to love their wives as their own bodies. He that loveth his wife loveth himself.
verses.verse_html: 28So ought men to love their wives as their own bodies. He that loveth his wife loveth himself.

verses.text_plain: For no man ever yet hated his own flesh; but nourisheth and cherisheth it, even as the Lord the church:
verses.verse_html: 29For no man ever yet hated his own flesh; but nourisheth and cherisheth it, even as the Lord the church:

verses.text_plain: For we are members of his body, of his flesh, and of his bones.
verses.verse_html: 30For we are members of his body, of his flesh, and of his bones.

verses.text_plain: For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother, and shall be joined unto his wife, and they two shall be one flesh.
verses.verse_html: 31For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother, and shall be joined unto his wife, and they two shall be one flesh.

verses.text_plain: This is a great mystery: but I speak concerning Christ and the church.
verses.verse_html: 32This is a great mystery: but I speak concerning Christ and the church.

verses.text_plain: Nevertheless let every one of you in particular so love his wife even as himself; and the wife see that she reverence her husband.
verses.verse_html: 33Nevertheless let every one of you in particular so love his wife even as himself; and the wife see that she reverence her husband.
